# Shared action (P#17): creates a product using an explicitly-passed bearer token — no closures
# over the caller (SPEC §8), so an admin token is a parameter, not implicit scope from a session
# (M14: callers pass a per-test fresh admin token rather than relying on the `admin` session's
# auto-applied header). Gives back the new product's id.

action create product(name, price, stock, categoryId, token)
  api POST /products body { name: {name}, price: {price}, stock: {stock}, categoryId: {categoryId} }
    header "Authorization" is "Bearer {token}"
  expect status equals 201
  capture body.id as id
  give id
